1
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:17,562
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language.)

2
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:27,744
(Ms. Praew Booking, 1 Person)

3
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:41,280
You look at her pictures every year.

4
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:44,840
Yes.

5
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:49,960
But this year, I don't think
I'll just be looking at pictures.

6
00:00:51,920 --> 00:00:54,280
Take care of your heart, too.

7
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,240
The person who loves the most

8
00:00:56,560 --> 00:00:58,960
will be the one who hurts the most.

9
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,800
I don't think it's that bad.

10
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:31,800
Hello, Miss Praew.

11
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,520
You've been away for a long time this time.

12
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:37,160
Hello, Mr. Jay.

13
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:40,080
I'm happy to see you every time I come.

14
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:44,000
I'm always in the same place.

15
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:46,840
I'm glad to meet you again, Ms. Praew.

16
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:50,680
Is my usual room with the mountain view
still available?

17
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:51,920
Yes.

18
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,000
Room 8

19
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,920
is always available for Ms. Praew.

20
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:57,720
I'll check for you.

21
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,280
Gosh!

22
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,240
Uh.

23
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:05,520
Is there something wrong?

24
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,600
Well...

25
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,760
The system

26
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,560
shows that room 8 has been double-booked.

27
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,120
So does that mean

28
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,360
there aren't any rooms left now?

29
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,600
Let me check again.

30
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,640
Hmm...

31
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,760
No rooms left at all, Ms. Praew.

32
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,640
A tour group has booked

33
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:31,080
the whole hotel.

34
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:35,560
So the only available room now is number 8.

35
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:38,680
But I...

36
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,560
Hold on.

37
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,080
I don't understand.

38
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,840
It shows that the booking for room 8
was made by the staff.

39
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,120
Ma'am,

40
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:52,400
did you secretly make the booking under my name?

41
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,200
Well...

42
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,280
Tonight, you have the night shift.

43
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:58,760
So I reserved a room for you.

44
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,560
Then I'll take a small room.

45
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,640
Any room will do.

46
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:08,400
No rooms left, Ms. Praew.

47
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:11,120
Currently, only room 8 is available.

48
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,800
Uh... It's not really a problem.

49
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,200
Jay, you can sleep

50
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,720
on the sofa in the back office.

51
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:21,080
And room 8 will go to the lady.

52
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,680
But during winter like this, there's a storm coming.

53
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:31,520
The power is flickering.

54
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:34,160
That room doesn't have air conditioning.

55
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,760
And it has no windows.

56
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,880
I probably couldn't breathe.

57
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:42,160
Or could the two of you share a room for now?

58
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:43,920
No.

59
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:45,920
I'm staff.

60
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,440
How can I share a room with guests?

61
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:49,600
Wouldn't that be strange?

62
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,960
It's not really a problem.

63
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,560
Our king-size room

64
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,520
is very large.

65
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,160
It has both a sofa and a partition

66
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:58,040
separating the bathroom and the bedroom.

67
00:03:58,440 --> 00:04:00,880
As long as the gentleman behaves himself,

68
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:02,840
it shouldn't be a problem.

69
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,320
Hmm...

70
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,600
But if you're not comfortable, Ms. Praew,

71
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:14,320
I'll find another solution.

72
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,000
It's okay.

73
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,640
It's just one night, right?

74
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:20,920
Yes.

75
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:22,960
Just one night.

76
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,840
I promise I won't cross any lines, Ms. Praew.

77
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,040
Okay.

78
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,720
I'll get you the key.

79
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,880
Here you go, Ms. Praew.

80
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,680
Thank you.

81
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:54,880
It gets super windy here during winter.

82
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,320
And the weather gets even colder.

83
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,400
It's still as beautiful as ever.

84
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,440
Yes, it is.

85
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:12,360
Still as beautiful.

86
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:22,120
Uh...

87
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,640
I think I'll just

88
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,400
prepare the bedding.

89
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,480
Jay.

90
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,560
Actually...

91
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:39,840
Well,

92
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,560
is there

93
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,440
a special package

94
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,520
called

95
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,480
Forced Romance or what?

96
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,000
Probably not

97
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,520
Forced Romance.

98
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:54,200
But I think it's more like a bonus from above.

99
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,800
I won't charge you extra.

100
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,200
That's great.

101
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,760
The lights are on now.

102
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,240
I think you should

103
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:05,800
take a warm shower first.

104
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,040
Okay.

105
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,520
Otherwise, the inverter might break down again.

106
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,240
Okay.

107
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,160
Please.

108
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,160
Thank you.

109
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:44,480
Well!

110
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,000
Uh!

111
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,520
Oh...

112
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:47,800
Sorry.

113
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:50,520
I forgot that you were in the room too.

114
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,840
I'm sorry too.

115
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:56,200
I didn't mean to look.

116
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,320
Yes.

117
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,600
I'll wait outside.

118
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:17,400
(Every storm is followed by clear skies
from someone who wants to see you smile)

119
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:21,200
(Every storm is followed by clear skies
from someone who wants to see you smile)

120
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,280
And then he said

121
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,920
he wanted to take a break.

122
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,040
A week later,

123
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,760
he posted a couple photo

124
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,920
with someone new in Japan.

125
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,520
I think

126
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,400
he doesn't deserve you as a girlfriend.

127
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,240
Jay, but...

128
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:00,840
You still don't

129
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:03,000
really know me that well.

130
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,360
I know you better than you think.

131
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:10,440
Are you secretly investigating clients?

132
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,680
Not at all.

133
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:24,440
But every winter when you stay here,

134
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:27,280
I see you

135
00:08:28,378 --> 00:08:29,538
working on the balcony,

136
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:32,194
sipping wine like this.

137
00:08:35,778 --> 00:08:37,058
Sometimes you smile,

138
00:08:38,858 --> 00:08:39,618
sometimes you cry.

139
00:08:43,818 --> 00:08:46,178
But you never forget to smile at the staff.

140
00:08:49,658 --> 00:08:52,256
I may not know you well enough.

141
00:08:55,138 --> 00:08:59,138
But I know you didn't deserve to be abandoned.

142
00:09:02,538 --> 00:09:03,498
Jay.

143
00:09:04,298 --> 00:09:06,818
If you say things like that,
a woman might get the wrong idea.

144
00:09:07,618 --> 00:09:09,218
Then feel free to get the right idea.

145
00:09:13,538 --> 00:09:14,618
Praew.

146
00:09:24,338 --> 00:09:25,618
I like you, Praew.

147
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:31,058
I've liked you since the first day we met.

148
00:09:55,898 --> 00:09:56,498
Uh...

149
00:09:58,218 --> 00:09:59,658
You can take the call first.

150
00:09:59,978 --> 00:10:02,418
I'll wait in the room.

151
00:10:02,738 --> 00:10:03,378
No.

152
00:10:06,738 --> 00:10:08,138
Not this time.

153
00:10:14,778 --> 00:10:16,898
Jay, do you know?

154
00:10:17,538 --> 00:10:20,018
I've decided to come back here again.

155
00:10:21,858 --> 00:10:23,858
I want to...

156
00:10:29,138 --> 00:10:33,378
throw this ring into the fountain.

157
00:10:33,818 --> 00:10:34,978
When I was driving here,

158
00:10:34,978 --> 00:10:38,738
I wasn't sure if I could do it.

159
00:10:44,098 --> 00:10:45,258
And now?

160
00:10:46,418 --> 00:10:50,138
Now I just want to start over

161
00:10:50,138 --> 00:10:52,978
with someone who truly sees me.

162
00:11:09,058 --> 00:11:12,778
Praew, it's okay to cry.

163
00:11:15,058 --> 00:11:16,978
You don't have to be strong today.

164
00:11:18,498 --> 00:11:20,738
It's okay to be weak.

165
00:11:28,858 --> 00:11:30,178
I don't want to do this

166
00:11:30,178 --> 00:11:31,978
in front of you.

167
00:11:32,538 --> 00:11:34,178
It's fine.

168
00:11:36,538 --> 00:11:38,138
I'm right here.

169
00:11:41,618 --> 00:11:43,378
There's no need to be afraid.

170
00:12:10,418 --> 00:12:11,938
Are you sure?

171
00:12:17,698 --> 00:12:19,978
In the past three years,

172
00:12:20,778 --> 00:12:24,298
thank you for the valuable relationship,

173
00:12:25,058 --> 00:12:26,938
and thank you for the lessons

174
00:12:26,938 --> 00:12:29,178
that made me realize

175
00:12:29,578 --> 00:12:32,000
I deserve better.

176
00:12:42,138 --> 00:12:43,938
Water splashed on your face.

177
00:12:45,856 --> 00:12:48,987
♪With quiet tears you'd never show♪

178
00:12:49,178 --> 00:12:51,645
♪Carrying love that disappeared♪

179
00:12:52,778 --> 00:12:53,858
Let's say this is

180
00:12:54,258 --> 00:12:56,338
an official new beginning.

181
00:12:59,578 --> 00:13:01,978
Can I ask for something?

182
00:13:02,898 --> 00:13:03,658
What is it?

183
00:13:05,978 --> 00:13:08,378
Could I be the first in line

184
00:13:09,098 --> 00:13:11,616
for your new love story?

185
00:13:12,346 --> 00:13:16,000
♪Maybe heaven let me stand this close♪

186
00:13:17,738 --> 00:13:18,698
Could I?

187
00:13:18,763 --> 00:13:21,632
♪And when the storm had hurt you most♪

188
00:13:21,632 --> 00:13:27,043
♪Be the arms where you could finally cry♪

189
00:13:28,570 --> 00:13:33,856
♪Let it fall, my love, let it go♪

190
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:37,163
♪The weight you carried far too long♪

191
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:39,232
♪You deserve a love that grows♪

192
00:13:39,232 --> 00:13:43,655
♪Not one that leaves you standing strong alone♪

193
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:47,212
♪Take my hand, you don't have to fight♪

194
00:13:47,392 --> 00:13:50,532
♪You don't have to prove you're brave♪

195
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:53,674
♪Let me be your safe tonight♪

196
00:13:53,696 --> 00:13:59,274
♪The vow your broken heart once prayed♪

197
00:14:01,978 --> 00:14:03,418
So this is

198
00:14:03,738 --> 00:14:07,648
the post-storm romance package, huh?

199
00:14:10,658 --> 00:14:11,818
No.

200
00:14:13,538 --> 00:14:15,872
This is off-menu, just for you alone.

201
00:14:15,872 --> 00:14:18,944
♪Tonight beneath these mountain skies♪

202
00:14:18,944 --> 00:14:21,822
♪The fountain waits for you to choose♪

203
00:14:22,007 --> 00:14:25,343
♪Not what you lost, not what you feared♪

204
00:14:25,452 --> 00:14:28,506
♪But what your healing heart can use♪

205
00:14:35,488 --> 00:14:38,240
♪I'll stand beside you through the cold♪

206
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:42,517
♪And warm your winters into May♪

207
00:14:45,466 --> 00:14:50,924
♪Let it fall, my love, let it fade♪

208
00:14:51,066 --> 00:14:53,908
♪The echo of a love untrue♪

209
00:14:54,195 --> 00:14:56,192
♪You were never meant to break♪

210
00:14:56,192 --> 00:14:59,488
♪You were meant to bloom, and I see you♪

211
00:14:59,488 --> 00:15:02,496
♪Here I am, not asking why♪

212
00:15:02,496 --> 00:15:06,629
♪Just choosing you, again and again♪

213
00:15:07,584 --> 00:15:10,016
♪If you let me stay tonight♪

214
00:15:10,016 --> 00:15:15,610
♪I'll love you like forever began♪

215
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:18,630
♪When the silver meets the water deep♪
